From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Wed, 24 Jun 2026 10:09:13 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] make: register make/gmake as an in-process brush builtin
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Recursive `$(MAKE)` (and configure/cmake-invoked make) now runs IN-PROCESS
instead of re-exec'ing the engine per sub-make. When brush runs `make`/`gmake`
it dispatches the new MakeBuiltin, which drives kati against the brush
ExecutionContext's LOGICAL state — working_dir from context.shell (resolved
with -C, no process chdir) and recipe output routed to context fd 1 — using
the per-instance Evaluator from the earlier de-globalization. In a -b box the
top-level make is dispatched the same way, so a recursive build now runs
entirely in ONE process: zero `make` rows (box test CASE 6).

Mechanism:
- kati exec.rs: recipe stdout goes through a thread-local sink (set_recipe_out)
  — process stdout by default, the builtin's context fd 1 when set.
- kati fileutil.rs: RecipeRunner is an Arc, cloned out with the lock RELEASED
  before invocation, so a recursive in-process make whose recipes re-enter
  run_with_installed_runner doesn't deadlock on the (non-reentrant) lock.
- brush.rs: BOX_RECIPE_CWD thread-local so recipes run at the make's logical
  working_dir, not the process cwd; MakeBuiltin (args already include argv[0],
  like the coreutils) + registration.
- katirun.rs: make_builtin entry (context-driven, no chdir, no exec); the
  recipe-runner install is factored out and shared with make_main.

Validated: box test MAKE-RS PASS (CASE 6 recursive make in-process added);
kati corpus KATI_COMPAT_PASS=364/378 fail=0; engine builds. The shadow/main()
path is untouched (used outside brush). KNOWN GAP: self-generating includes
(remake) aren't yet handled by the builtin — in-process remake loop is next.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
